<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,153,251]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,227,153,179]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Notes:</emphasis>
A widespread species generally uncommonly collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[878,947,153,179]" name="Georgia" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Iberia</collectingCountry>
. However, the species is known from Andalucía (
<bibRefCitation author="Dardon, M. J. &amp; Torres, F. &amp; Ornosa, C." box="[267,419,189,215]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" pagination="467 - 497" refId="ref20799" refString="Dardon, M. J., Torres, F. &amp; Ornosa, C. (2014) The subgenus Andrena (Micrandrena) (Hymenoptera: Andrenidae) in the Iberian Peninsula. Zootaxa, 3872, 467 - 497. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3872.5.3" type="journal article" year="2014">Dardon 2014</bibRefCitation>
) and it may generally be overlooked and under-recorded. Another species that is narrowly oligolectic on 
<taxonomicName authority="(Westrich 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Westrich" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[358,705,225,251]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Ornithogalum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[358,517,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Ornithogalum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich, P." box="[531,697,225,251]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref23439" refString="Westrich, P. (2010) Untersuchungen zum Blutenbesuch von Bienen (Hymenoptera, Apidae) an Ornithogalum s. l. (Milchstern, Hyacinthaceae). Eucera, 3, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="2010">Westrich 2010</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
which may contribute to its previous lack of records.
</paragraph>
